    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, can you help me understand the difference between a \"confidentiality period\" and a \"survival clause\" in a standard contract? I'm trying to make sure I don't miss anything important.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely. A \"confidentiality period\" refers to the time during which parties to the contract are obliged to keep certain information confidential. This can include private details or trade secrets that are not to be shared with third parties. On the other hand, a \"survival clause\" generally ensures that certain terms or obligations of the contract continue to exist beyond the completion of the contract itself, providing continued protection or benefits.",
